  <datafield tag="500" ind1=" " ind2=" ">
    <subfield code="a">Wendell Phillips received a letter from Maria Weston Chapman enclosing the letters of (Dominique Francois) Arago, (A.C.E.) Leflo, and (J.B.A.) Charras, and containing remarks of these &quot;as related to our refusal of oath.&quot; Wendell Phillips wants to translate the letters for the Liberator and preface them with Mrs. Chapman&apos;s remarks. Wendell Phillips asks Anne Warren Weston: &quot;Would it do to let them appear as hers or shall they seem homespun?&quot;</subfield>
  </datafield>
  <datafield tag="500" ind1=" " ind2=" ">
